Here are both approaches:

**1. Register the route** (`AppShell.xaml.cs`):
```csharp
Routing.RegisterRoute("productdetails", typeof(ProductDetailsPage));
```

**2. Navigate from ProductListPage** (e.g., on CollectionView selection):

```csharp
// Approach A — string query parameter
await Shell.Current.GoToAsync($"productdetails?productId={product.Id}");

// Approach B — pass the full object
var parameters = new ShellNavigationQueryParameters
{
    { "product", product }
};
await Shell.Current.GoToAsync("productdetails", parameters);
```

**3. Receive on the ViewModel** with `IQueryAttributable`:

```csharp
public class ProductDetailsViewModel : ObservableObject, IQueryAttributable
{
    private string _productId;
    private Product _product;

    public string ProductId
    {
        get => _productId;
        set => SetProperty(ref _productId, value);
    }

    public Product Product
    {
        get => _product;
        set => SetProperty(ref _product, value);
    }

    public void ApplyQueryAttributes(IDictionary<string, object> query)
    {
        // Approach A — string parameter arrives as a string
        if (query.TryGetValue("productId", out var id))
        {
            ProductId = id.ToString();
            // Load full product from a service using the ID...
        }

        // Approach B — complex object arrives as-is
        if (query.TryGetValue("product", out var obj) && obj is Product p)
        {
            Product = p;
            ProductId = p.Id;
        }
    }
}
```

**Key differences:**

| | String query param | `ShellNavigationQueryParameters` |
|---|---|---|
| **Syntax** | `$"route?key={val}"` | `new ShellNavigationQueryParameters { ... }` |
| **Data types** | Strings only | Any object |
| **URI visible** | Yes (good for deep links) | No (in-memory only) |
| **Use when** | You have a simple ID to look up | You already have the object in memory |

> **Tip:** Always `await` `GoToAsync` — fire-and-forget causes race conditions. And make sure the ViewModel is set as `BindingContext` on `ProductDetailsPage` (ideally via DI) so `IQueryAttributable` is discovered automatically by Shell.
